input: Country: France. Purchaser Name: EDF SA. Summary: Renewal of the Corporate and Nominative Payment Card Market for Edf Group Employees. Description: The purpose of this contract is the supply and management of individual and nominative corporate payment cards, as well as associated services, intended for business travel and specific general expenses of the Group's employees. EDF. The means of payment concern in particular professional expenses not subject to centralized payment via the Group's Travel tools (additional services, catering, taxis, fuel, miscellaneous costs). The market applies to entities of the EDF Group, mainly in France (mainland and DROM-COM), as well as internationally, particularly for certain European subsidiaries. The beneficiaries of the cards are EDF Group employees required to travel professionals. In accordance with the provisions of article R.2162-4 of the Public Procurement Code, and the requirements of European Directive 2014/25/EU, this framework agreement is accompanied by a maximum volume without commitment set at 30,000 cards active over the total duration of the framework agreement. This ceiling is set exclusively in order to satisfy the capping obligations imposed by European public procurement law. It is expressly specified that this volume is strictly provisional, that it in no way constitutes a contractual commitment for the Company and that it cannot give right to any compensation for the benefit of the holders. input: Country: France. Purchaser Name: RTE - TRANSPORT ELECTRICITY NETWORK. Summary: Broker to Support the Sale of an Rte Battery Energy Storage System. Description: In a context of the emergence of stationary storage systems, RTE (manager of the Electricity Transmission Network in France) launched a project in 2016 aimed at experimenting with the use of several storage sites (Electricity Storage System by Battery or Battery Energy Storage System - BESS). In particular, the so-called RINGO project aimed to test and qualify the use of this type of battery to manage local congestion on the HTB1 network, via demonstrators. experimental directly connected to the French General Transport Network. It was decided that the project would be deployed on three sites, which were selected because of their short-term exposure to transit constraints, constraints linked to the rapid installation of wind or photovoltaic production on the MV network in particular. Each selected site thus includes: •Batteries with a total power of 10 to 12 MW and an energy storage capacity of 24 to 33 MWh; •Of the control, command and communication equipment, in particular with the RTE IS application chain allowing battery management; •Power electronics equipment and equipment allowing voltage transformation between the batteries and the general network. input: Country: France. Purchaser Name: LOGEAL IMMOBILIERE. Summary: Service Contract for Assistance Services to the Project Management of a Shared Global Insurance Market for the 8 Lessor Members of Normandy Territory and Habitat. Description: Market for insurance services, assistance and advice<br> This call for tenders is concluded in the form of a contract in installments.<br> The firm portion concerns the 8 members of Territoire and Habitat Normand.<br> Then, the optional tranches will be activated by the members lessors according to their respective needs.<br> The service provider will be required to intervene in the Normandy region which is covered by the 8 lessor members of Territoire and Habitat Normand.<br> SINGLE LOT<br> - Firm tranche: from the award notification until December 31, 2026: preparation a study of the opportunity for pooling and therefore the preparation of the consultation file for companies to be drawn up, consequently determining the contractual arrangement of a global pooled insurance market from 2027 to 2030 inclusive, and monitoring of the competitive bidding procedure, analysis of offers submitted, until notification of award (generally, the end of this mission will occur on 12/31/2026). The firm tranche concerns the 8 donor members.<br> - Optional tranche: from January 1, 2027 to December 31, 2030 inclusive and assistance with the management of contracts and claims relating to these contracts.
